"script": "Ordinary college students were split into two groups, prisoners and guards, for a simple two-week experiment in a fake basement jail. At first it felt like a game. But within days, something disturbing happened. The guards started inventing cruel punishments, humiliating the prisoners, stripping away their names and replacing them with numbers. And the prisoners broke down, some sobbing, others rebelling. The shift was so fast and so brutal that they shut the whole thing down after just six days. The terrifying lesson? Give normal people a uniform and a little power, and they can turn cruel almost overnight.",
